    "title": "US Slag Cement Sources - Blast Furnace Slag from Integrated Steel Mills",
    "description": "Integrated steel mills with blast furnaces producing granulated blast furnace slag (GBFS/GGBFS) for use as supplementary cementitious material",
    "data_sources": ["USGS Iron and Steel Mineral Commodity Summary", "AIST Directory of Iron and Steel Plants", "Slag Cement Association", "Company reports"],
    "last_updated": "2026-02-14",
    "naics_code": "331110",
    "astm_standard": "ASTM C989 - Standard Specification for Slag Cement for Use in Concrete and Mortars",
    "notes": "Slag cement (GGBFS) is a byproduct of blast furnace ironmaking. Only integrated mills with blast furnaces produce slag suitable for cement. Electric arc furnace (EAF) steel mills do not produce cementitious slag. US BF capacity has been declining as EAF share grows."
  },
